## ⌨️ Keyboard Shortcuts in Databricks

| **Shortcut** | **Action** |
|--------------|------------|
| **Esc + B new cell below and + A for new cell above the current poiting cell
| **Ctrl + Enter** | Run current cell |
| **Shift + Enter** | Run cell and move to next |
| **Alt + Enter** | Run cell and insert new one below |
| **Ctrl + /** | Toggle comment for selected lines |
| **Ctrl + Shift + -** | Split cell at cursor |
| **Ctrl + Shift + F** | Search across notebook |
| **Ctrl + Shift + P** | Open command palette (quick actions) |
| **Ctrl + Shift + L** | Toggle line numbers |
| **Ctrl + B** | Toggle sidebar visibility |
| **Ctrl + D** | Duplicate current line |
| **Ctrl + Z / Ctrl + Y** | Undo / Redo |

---

## 📌 Tips for Effective Use
- Use **%md cells** to document steps directly in your notebook for better collaboration.  
- Combine **%sql** with visualization features to quickly plot query results.  
- Use **%fs** to manage files in DBFS without leaving the notebook.  
- Keyboard shortcuts save time when running multiple cells or editing large notebooks.  
- **%lsmagic** is handy to discover hidden or less‑used commands.  

---

## ✅ Why It Matters
By mastering **magic commands** and **shortcuts**, you can make Databricks notebooks more interactive, reduce repetitive tasks, and improve productivity — especially when handling large datasets or collaborating across teams.
